how do i get a feral cat to trust me without trapping it ive done the basic stuff like put food out for it but anytime i come near it it runs if you eventually get the cat to trust you here's little tip i have a feral cat living with me and he has been a great friend for many years but here's a note do not try to turn the cat into a normal house pet since the cat is wild we do not actualy own him if you eventually get the cat to trust you enough to take it indoors occasianaly you still have to let it go outside and do its wild duties the feral cat i have is more like a guest at my house than a permanent resident sometimes he stays inside with us but then he'll leave outside to hunt oh also don't be alarmed if the cat decides to leave you little dead gifts on your porch you have to understand that the cat won't want his her freedom taken away Cat Feral cat Socialization Bobcat Hamster Domestication Feral cat colony Shaggy dog story Electrophysiology Animal rights Island Fox Dog Lady and the Tramp Fancy rat Introduced species Pet skunk Hunting Domestic rabbit Ferret Black Books Friends Trailer Park Boys RuneScape quests Garfield Water Buffalo House Taboo food and drink Year of the Spider Zagreus (Doctor Who audio) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Shannara creatures Houston Astros Honeybee KROQ Top 106.7 Countdown of 1988 Puma Poker jargon Domestic pig Island restoration Cheetah Animal Collective Kakapo Phoebe Buffay's songs Wild Cat John Frusciante Tag The Dalek Invasion of Earth Viva La Bam The Lovely Bones Tai shogi Cat on a Hot Tin Roof The League of Gentlemen (comedy) Dr. Seuss Hellsing Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Leopard Feral child The Critic Social rule Glossary of firefighting terms Livestock Neighbours One Piece minor characters Aladdin (1992 film) Cats (musical) Kevin and Kell Dai dai shogi The Fellowship of the Ring Black Cat (comics) St. Louis Cardinals The End of the World (Doctor Who) Vegeta V (TV series) Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) 